HEADWORD: Hypoptilum
<hw>Hy*pop"ti*lum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> L. <plw>Hypoptila</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, E.
<plw>Hypoptilums</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>"ypo`</grk> beneath + <?/ down.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An
accessory plume arising from the posterior side of the stem of the
contour feathers of many birds; -- called also
<altname>aftershaft</altname>. See <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Feather</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
